2
00:01:39.500 --> 00:01:44.000
Cacao Island

3
00:01:43.930 --> 00:01:47.050
The Straw Hat crew's
planned rendezvous at Cacao Island

4
00:01:46.210 --> 00:01:50.970
12:28 a.m.

5
00:01:47.050 --> 00:01:49.200
is in 32 minutes.

6
00:01:50.950 --> 00:01:52.550
Nobody has come out yet.

7
00:01:51.220 --> 00:01:55.260
One Last Thing

8
00:01:52.550 --> 00:01:55.250
I guess the battle is dragging on.

9
00:01:55.250 --> 00:01:58.360
Is there any chance that
Big Brother Katakuri might lose?

10
00:01:58.360 --> 00:02:01.810
What?! You think there's
a chance Katakuri might lose?!

11
00:02:01.810 --> 00:02:04.010
Newji! Are you...

12
00:02:04.010 --> 00:02:05.980
serious?!

13
00:02:06.610 --> 00:02:09.150
The chance of that is zero!

14
00:02:09.150 --> 00:02:10.310
Ouch!

15
00:02:10.310 --> 00:02:16.220
Why did you hit me?! I'm Newsan!
I wasn't the one who said that!

16
00:02:16.220 --> 00:02:20.000
Katakuri will never be defeated
for the rest of his life!

17
00:02:20.420 --> 00:02:22.830
He's right, you idiot!

18
00:02:22.830 --> 00:02:26.630
Big Brother Katakuri is a perfect man!

19
00:02:26.630 --> 00:02:30.050
Ouch! I'm Newshi!

20
00:02:30.050 --> 00:02:32.720
I'm sorry, Newsan, Newshi...

21
00:02:33.740 --> 00:02:35.170
Ouch!

22
00:02:35.170 --> 00:02:36.540
That's what you get!

23
00:02:36.540 --> 00:02:37.950
What?!

24
00:02:37.950 --> 00:02:39.540
You idiot! You idiot!

25
00:02:39.540 --> 00:02:43.730
But... he hasn't contacted us in a while...
It's strange.

26
00:02:43.730 --> 00:02:46.750
If I were Straw Hat, here's what I would do:

27
00:02:46.750 --> 00:02:50.400
he is planning to rendezvous with his crew
at one a.m., here on Cacao Island.

28
00:02:50.950 --> 00:02:56.370
In other words,
his crew won't arrive until one a.m...

29
00:02:56.370 --> 00:03:01.710
If I were in his shoes, I'd capture Sister Brûlée,
the only key to the Mirro-world,

30
00:03:01.710 --> 00:03:06.550
and wait out the clock
in the Mirro-world or on other islands!

31
00:03:06.550 --> 00:03:11.300
That makes sense!
Sister Brûlée is currently missing, after all!

32
00:03:11.300 --> 00:03:12.430
That's right!

33
00:03:12.430 --> 00:03:17.390
In other words, it's highly likely that Straw Hat Luffy
will try and run away from his duel with Katakuri...

34
00:03:17.390 --> 00:03:21.870
and come out of this mirror at one a.m. sharp...

35
00:03:21.870 --> 00:03:23.480
I see... I agree.

36
00:03:23.480 --> 00:03:27.400
Sister Brûlée is a bit dense,
so she's easy to capture.

37
00:03:27.400 --> 00:03:31.880
Akimeg, our sister might be listening
through the mirror.

38
00:03:31.880 --> 00:03:33.450
Oh, oops!

39
00:03:33.450 --> 00:03:37.170
We've got 30 minutes...
We need to stay alert.

40
00:03:37.170 --> 00:03:39.750
Hurry up and come out, Straw Hat!

41
00:03:39.750 --> 00:03:43.500
I'll chop you in half with my sickle!

42
00:04:00.640 --> 00:04:03.600
Are they all fighters?

43
00:04:03.600 --> 00:04:07.980
Seems like that's the only mirror
that they left intact...

44
00:04:11.190 --> 00:04:14.650
When Luffy comes out,
we need to leave immediately...

45
00:04:14.650 --> 00:04:17.320
or both of us will be killed...

46
00:04:19.620 --> 00:04:24.080
When Luffy comes out,
that'll be when we part ways...

47
00:04:24.080 --> 00:04:25.210
Pudding-cha...

48
00:04:25.960 --> 00:04:27.830
So far away!

49
00:04:27.830 --> 00:04:30.360
Can you hear me, Pudding-chan ?

50
00:04:30.360 --> 00:04:33.610
D-D-D... Don't look at me!

51
00:04:33.610 --> 00:04:35.970
I-I-I am listening to you!

52
00:04:35.970 --> 00:04:37.200
Sanji...

53
00:04:37.200 --> 00:04:38.470
...-san !

54
00:04:41.890 --> 00:04:45.180
Looking back, we sure met
during unusual circumstances...

55
00:04:51.270 --> 00:04:56.530
This is your bride-to-be...
Madam Charlotte Pudding!

56
00:04:56.860 --> 00:04:59.960
Let's get married tomorrow.

57
00:05:03.970 --> 00:05:07.350
I had a lot of fun with you, Pudding-chan,

58
00:05:07.350 --> 00:05:10.270
but it's almost time for us to say goodbye.

59
00:05:10.270 --> 00:05:11.730
Thank you for everything!

60
00:05:19.570 --> 00:05:24.630
I fooled you and tried to kill you...

61
00:05:24.630 --> 00:05:27.370
So don't thank me, Sanji-san !

62
00:05:27.370 --> 00:05:30.660
I want to apologize!

63
00:05:30.660 --> 00:05:34.040
I really need to apologize!

64
00:05:52.270 --> 00:05:54.000
Shut up!

65
00:05:57.480 --> 00:06:01.610
No! No! I did it again!

66
00:06:01.610 --> 00:06:05.110
You're right!
We're enemies, after all!

67
00:06:05.650 --> 00:06:09.430
To you, Pudding-chan,
our marriage was just a trap.

68
00:06:09.430 --> 00:06:14.620
The whole thing was staged
by the Big Mom Pirates...

69
00:06:17.420 --> 00:06:18.420
But...

70
00:06:19.250 --> 00:06:21.710
maybe it was unpleasant
for you, Pudding-chan...

71
00:06:24.540 --> 00:06:28.640
but I'm glad that you were the one
in the role of my fiancée, Pudding-chan !

72
00:06:41.070 --> 00:06:43.070
Ah, no...

73
00:06:43.430 --> 00:06:46.720
I'm sorry! I didn't mean to insult you!

74
00:06:46.720 --> 00:06:49.130
No! Stop crying!

75
00:06:49.130 --> 00:06:50.660
Stop, tears!

76
00:06:50.660 --> 00:06:52.470
I-I'm sorry!

77
00:06:52.470 --> 00:06:54.920
I didn't mean that, Pudding-chan !

78
00:06:56.290 --> 00:06:58.440
H-Hey, Sanji...

79
00:06:58.440 --> 00:06:59.880
...-san...

80
00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:03.880
Could you do me a favor?!

81
00:07:05.340 --> 00:07:09.220
Just one last thing...

82
00:07:11.220 --> 00:07:13.620
This is all I ask of you!

83
00:07:30.700 --> 00:07:33.950
12:37 a.m.

84
00:08:40.060 --> 00:08:43.550
Whole Cake Island

85
00:08:42.690 --> 00:08:46.110
I can't believe they've survived this long!

86
00:08:43.610 --> 00:08:46.110
12:40 a.m.

87
00:08:46.110 --> 00:08:48.160
The Straw Hat crew...

88
00:08:48.160 --> 00:08:52.220
If they're able to escape
from such an all-out attack formation,

89
00:08:52.220 --> 00:08:54.700
it'll be unbelievably big news!

90
00:08:54.700 --> 00:08:58.590
Shut up, Morgans!
You won't be getting a scoop!

91
00:08:58.590 --> 00:09:01.310
In order to ensure we avoid that,

92
00:09:01.310 --> 00:09:05.400
we swallowed our pride
and sent a horde of soldiers to Cacao Island!

93
00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:10.710
Even if Gold Roger, the former pirate king,
were to come out of the mirror,

94
00:09:10.710 --> 00:09:13.300
he wouldn't be able to escape!

95
00:09:13.300 --> 00:09:17.370
Once we catch them all, we'll execute them
and line up their heads for display;

96
00:09:17.370 --> 00:09:20.350
you should put that
on the front page tomorrow.

97
00:09:20.850 --> 00:09:22.490
It'll serve as a warning!

98
00:09:24.230 --> 00:09:27.770
How vulgar...
There's no need to go that far.

99
00:09:28.860 --> 00:09:31.630
Don't be silly!
It's almost too kind!

100
00:09:32.400 --> 00:09:34.800
We'll get good news soon!

101
00:09:34.800 --> 00:09:40.040
There's no way that one ship can
get through our gigantic fleet!

102
00:09:42.250 --> 00:09:45.270
12:43 a.m.

103
00:09:46.460 --> 00:09:48.550
Wait!

104
00:09:49.230 --> 00:09:52.720
Bege's Ship
At Sea

105
00:09:50.050 --> 00:09:52.720
Give me the cake!

106
00:09:54.340 --> 00:09:56.180
The sails are on fire!

107
00:09:56.180 --> 00:09:58.350
Put it out now! We're gonna sink!

108
00:10:00.310 --> 00:10:03.760
We can't go on-rero, Father!
This is the end-rero !

109
00:10:03.760 --> 00:10:06.780
We're gonna die before we
reach the island-rero !

110
00:10:06.780 --> 00:10:09.480
Let's throw the cake off and flee, Father!

111
00:10:10.020 --> 00:10:12.110
Don't falter now!

112
00:10:12.110 --> 00:10:13.360
Rero ?

113
00:10:14.560 --> 00:10:18.830
We may have all come
from different places,

114
00:10:18.830 --> 00:10:20.830
but in the face of death,

115
00:10:20.830 --> 00:10:23.580
we should stick together!

116
00:10:23.600 --> 00:10:26.420
Father!

117
00:10:27.710 --> 00:10:28.960
I see it!

118
00:10:32.760 --> 00:10:34.260
It's Puffs Island!

119
00:10:34.260 --> 00:10:36.140
Rero !

120
00:10:36.140 --> 00:10:40.100
We're almost there!
Stay strong, guys!

121
00:10:40.100 --> 00:10:44.520
Yeah!

122
00:10:45.380 --> 00:10:48.900
12:45 a.m.

123
00:10:50.580 --> 00:10:53.760
We'll make it by one a.m.,
just as we promised!

124
00:10:55.050 --> 00:10:59.270
But what I'm worried about is the key
to escaping the Mirro-world: Brûlée.

125
00:10:59.270 --> 00:11:04.150
Even if Luffy wins,
he can't get out of there without Brûlée!

126
00:11:04.150 --> 00:11:08.900
I don't think Luffy is the type of person
who can think that far ahead...

127
00:11:08.900 --> 00:11:10.940
You're right! He can't!

128
00:11:10.940 --> 00:11:13.360
He definitely can't!
What should we do?!

129
00:11:13.360 --> 00:11:16.640
First of all, we don't even know
if he knows the current time...

130
00:11:16.640 --> 00:11:18.100
That too?!

131
00:11:18.610 --> 00:11:20.720
So much could go wrong...

132
00:11:21.830 --> 00:11:23.950
but we believe in you, Luffy!

133
00:11:27.740 --> 00:11:30.010
12:47 a.m.

134
00:11:54.470 --> 00:11:57.570
Even when he falls, he falls forward...

135
00:12:12.650 --> 00:12:14.690
Listen carefully, Luffy!

136
00:12:15.190 --> 00:12:17.900
At the earliest, we'll arrive in 10 hours!

137
00:12:17.900 --> 00:12:19.490
That's around one a.m.!

138
00:12:19.500 --> 00:12:22.890
So after you beat that guy up,

139
00:12:22.890 --> 00:12:25.930
search for a mirror that leads to Cacao Island!

140
00:12:25.930 --> 00:12:27.980
We'll meet you there!

141
00:12:31.500 --> 00:12:34.330
What time is it right now?

142
00:13:01.990 --> 00:13:04.160
Someday... will you...

143
00:13:06.740 --> 00:13:09.410
come back here to defeat Big Mom?

144
00:13:13.830 --> 00:13:15.920
Of course! I am the man

145
00:13:15.920 --> 00:13:18.680
who will be king of the pirates!

146
00:13:31.640 --> 00:13:34.430
You're seeing pretty far into the future...

147
00:14:34.120 --> 00:14:37.140
Branch, let's go...

148
00:14:37.420 --> 00:14:39.290
What? Branch?

149
00:14:39.960 --> 00:14:42.170
She escaped!

150
00:14:42.170 --> 00:14:45.550
Oh, no! I can't
get out of here without her...

151
00:14:45.550 --> 00:14:47.220
W-What should I do?

152
00:14:49.310 --> 00:14:51.010
I don't have time...

153
00:14:51.010 --> 00:14:53.770
Big Brother!

154
00:14:54.730 --> 00:14:58.730
Big Brother Katakuri!

155
00:14:59.860 --> 00:15:01.030
Branch!

156
00:15:01.030 --> 00:15:03.710
The name's Brûlée, Straw Hat!

157
00:15:03.710 --> 00:15:07.240
What foul tricks did you use
to take down my big brother?!

158
00:15:07.240 --> 00:15:09.860
So you were able to defeat Katakuri!

159
00:15:09.860 --> 00:15:11.990
I can't believe it!

160
00:15:12.000 --> 00:15:13.330
You're...

161
00:15:16.500 --> 00:15:19.300
I am... Nazoms!

162
00:15:16.500 --> 00:15:18.730
Nazo: Mysterious

